title: Homestead Survivor Video
description: This video stars the entire "cast" of Homestead, Inc. back in the Fall of 2001. The Survivor theme was inspired by the impending layoffs that forced the company to lay off about 15% of our friends, but ultimately helped the company survive the "bubble". Alenda Chang, Stephanie Wong, and Felicia Jose star in the video, which was filmed and edited Randy Lau, with camera work by the lovely (and talented) Stella Hwang. Thanks to Destiny's Child and Beyonce Knowles for the music, which they didn't technically authorize us to use :)

title: Phoenix Vigil in Support of Cindy Sheehan
description: My wife, daughter and I showed our support for Cindy Sheehan, the mother of the late Casey Sheehan, who died in 2004 in Iraq in service to our country. We weere part of  one of more than 1,400 candlelight vigils tonight across the United States. Sheehan is camped outside President Bush’s home in Crawford, Texas, waiting for a chance to speak to him about her son... wanting to know his life was not lost in vain.        We went to the vigil held at 24th Street and Camelback in Phoenix. It was a peaceful yet vocal protest. There were candles, placards and cheers as cars went by honking their horns in support.        The footage here is raw. I wanted to approximate the feel of the event. Whether or not you agree with Sheehan, you have to admire her courage and the strength of those who came out on a 99-degree evening to show their support.        By the way, I beat the local TV news by more than an hour with this footage!

title: Falun Gong Protest in NY
description: On 7th Avenue in New York City, we encountered a peaceful and meaningful protest of the persecution of millions of followers of Falun Gong in China. title: c'était un rendez-vous
description: On an August morning in 1978, French filmmaker Claude Lelouch mounted a gyro-stabilized camera to the bumper of a Ferrari 275 GTB and had a friend, a professional Formula 1 racer, drive at breakneck speed through the heart of Paris. The film was limited for technical reasons to 10 minutes; the course was from Porte Dauphine, through the Louvre, to the Basilica of Sacre Coeur.  No streets were closed, for Lelouch was unable to obtain a permit.  The driver completed the course in about 9 minutes, reaching nearly 140 MPH in some stretches. The footage reveals him running real red lights, nearly hitting real pedestrians, and driving the wrong way up real one-way streets.  Upon showing the film in public for the first time, Lelouch was arrested. He has never revealed the identity of the driver, and the film went underground until a DVD release a few years ago.  Now, thanks to the miracle of the Internets, you can watch it in your browser.

title: c'était un rendez-vous
description: On an August morning in 1978, French filmmaker Claude Lelouch mounted a gyro-stabilized camera to the bumper of a Ferrari 275 GTB and had a friend, a professional Formula 1 racer, drive at breakneck speed through the heart of Paris. The film was limited for technical reasons to 10 minutes; the course was from Porte Dauphine, through the Louvre, to the Basilica of Sacre Coeur.  No streets were closed, for Lelouch was unable to obtain a permit.  The driver completed the course in about 9 minutes, reaching nearly 140 MPH in some stretches. The footage reveals him running real red lights, nearly hitting real pedestrians, and driving the wrong way up real one-way streets.  Upon showing the film in public for the first time, Lelouch was arrested. He has never revealed the identity of the driver, and the film went underground until a DVD release a few years ago.  Now, thanks to the miracle of the Internets, you can watch it in your browser.

title: Baker Christmas Demo
description: The third annual Baker Christmas Demo totally went in downtown Los Angeles. A full two or three thousand Kids showed up to watch Emerica pros Andrew Reynolds, Kevin “Spanky” Long, Leo Romero and am Braydon Szafranski obliterate the street course with their Baker teammates.  The demo was set up in conjunction with the Doogood Conservatory to help under-privileged kids during the holiday season. Three thousand canned food items were donated by skaters in return for raffle tickets to the world’s largest product giveaway!  A huge truckload of product was given out to a colossal crowd, and if you had a raffle ticket, you most likely walked away with a Baker deck and some Emerica apparel, at the very least. Emerica shoe certificates and other product were also given out.

I had my lyrics on the computer because, as always, I forget them.. so she had the mouse, scrolling down the page. she also pressed record on my camera for me C= props to Sierra, my 12 year old recording girl. anyhow, it's cut short because my little cousin Ben who is about 6 came running upstairs and knocked on my door, so I guess I'll have to make another one later haha. enjoy.  pee.ess: comments are lovely C= AND I know it sounds mumble-y.. please be nice, I need better stuff, I know. Also, a the end, there was another verse but I had to cut it out because there wasn't that much time on my camera left.. confusing, but that's why it sounds bad. LYRICS ON PROFILE.

title: The Winning Ticket
description: For the second year in a row, Thad's friends planned a prank to make him think he won the lottery. They taped a previous night's lottery drawing and then bought a lottery ticket to match those winning numbers. They had him buy his own lottery tickets, then they swapped it out with the fake ticket. They played the pre-recorded drawing as Thad checked his numbers. If you ever wanted to know what it feels like to win the lottery, this gives you a pretty good idea...

This year no Cannon Gun was fired by Tam the Gun (look him up on Google) he died, so for the first New Year in many years there was no gun fired on the hour chime, Tam's whisky lay waiting and a lone piper played as the Fireworks went off as a mark of respect.

title: Hogmanay Live! - Happy New Year 2006 from Scotland
description: Hogmanay Live! - Happy New Year 2006 from Scotland. Hosted by Jackie Bird (BBC Scotland News anchor) and Donny Monroe formally lead singer of the band Runrig - See the fireworks go off Live from Edinburgh castle, normally the biggest New year party in the world. This year no Cannon Gun was fired by the infamous Tam the Gun, in real life known as, Staff Sergeant Thomas McKay, known as Tam the Gun, died at his home early on Thursday morning, 17th November 2005 at the age of 60. He had been suffering from cancer. :-( So for the first Scottish New Year in many years there was no gun fired on the hour chime, Tam's whisky lay waiting on top on the Cannon, and a lone piper played as the Fireworks went off as a mark of respect to Tam. He will be sadly missed here. But we still had the best Hogmanay (New years Eve) party in the world, as always we Scots know how to hold a party,people come here every New year from all over Europe and the rest of the world just for the all night party, we are a proud nation and we keep our traditions and heritage, and are proud of it. Enjoy the video, sorry I wanted to show all, but YouTube only allow 100 MB max, and my Video exceeded that, compressing the video only made the quality really bad, so it's best this way. The beginning brings a tear to the eyes... Happy New Year 2006, and thanks for all your kind comments. I really didn't expect any hits, and placed it here only for my blog, so I'm very overwhelmed by the huge hits. You can read more about Tam the Gun on the BBC news website here: http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/4446374.stm

title: Hogmanay Live! - Happy New Year 2006 from Scotland
description: Hogmanay Live! - Happy New Year 2006 from Scotland. Hosted by Jackie Bird (BBC Scotland News anchor) and Donny Monroe formally lead singer of the band Runrig - See the fireworks go off Live from Edinburgh castle, normally the biggest New year party in the world. This year no Cannon Gun was fired by the infamous Tam the Gun, in real life known as, Staff Sergeant Thomas McKay, known as Tam the Gun, died at his home early on Thursday morning, 17th November 2005 at the age of 60. He had been suffering from cancer. :-( So for the first Scottish New Year in many years there was no gun fired on the hour chime, Tam's whisky lay waiting on top on the Cannon, and a lone piper played as the Fireworks went off as a mark of respect to Tam. He will be sadly missed here. But we still had the best Hogmanay (New years Eve) party in the world, as always we Scots know how to hold a party,people come here every New year from all over Europe and the rest of the world just for the all night party, we are a proud nation and we keep our traditions and heritage, and are proud of it. Enjoy the video, sorry I wanted to show all, but YouTube only allow 100 MB max, and my Video exceeded that, compressing the video only made the quality really bad, so it's best this way. The beginning brings a tear to the eyes... Happy New Year 2006, and thanks for all your kind comments. I really didn't expect any hits, and placed it here only for my blog, so I'm very overwhelmed by the huge hits. PS, to the rest of you, thanks ;) PPS, I love YouTube.com... seriously, I do!  xoxo, www.dearcrissy.com Crissy

This film was made by Eric Norcross and Francisco Pina and stars: Kevin Gall, Chris Diaz, Jack Moran, John Tully, Greg Vorob, Shareef Mcintosh, Dawn Simons, Robert Youngren and others.  YES--I do aspire to be a mainstream filmmaker, maybe that's why people are commenting positively about it.  I don't know--but what do you expect?  A video made by an amateur who has little interest in being mainstream and professional--or a video made by someone looking to acquire gigs--which is going to look better?  The cliche' remark was un-called for.  This is far from cliche'.

title: Our Crazy Hamster Dance Video
description: With help from our family & friends, the newest funniest Hamster Dance out to date.  Serious, check us out,  PLEASE RATE US & LEAVE COMMENTS - we would love to hear from you !!!  Or email me at photomama5@sbcglobal.net or join our MYSPACE group at http://groups.myspace.com/photomama !!  Also - if you are interested in more info on the original Hamster Dance go to HAMSTERDANCE2.com  They rock.  To answer some of your questions - yes doing it in public is CRAZY.  People kept laughing at us, and staring, and some people didn't care.  It was a lot of fun!  One of the scenes in the video we were in a GLASS elevator, so each level people were staring and laughing it was soo funny.  Then .. in the middle of Sam's Club breakdancing, that was the ultimate!  Enjoy!  New answer to question :  why Master Chief from Halo in the middle of the video?  CUZ MASTER CHIEF AND HALO ROCK!! DUH!

title: Marked Trailer
description: Marked is the story of two starting-out, yet gifted hitmen, plunged right into the biggest mystery of their lives, one which could prove fatal if not handled with care. A film-noir action mystery by Studio San Pica. Studio San Pica was formed in August of 2005 by two college students named Kyle Hekhuis and Dane Svenningsen. Marked is SSP's first film. Once the film is completed, it will be submitted to film festivals across the country, and possibly the world...

title: Our Crazy Hamster Dance Video
description: With help from our family & friends, the newest funniest Hamster Dance out to date.  Serious, check us out,  PLEASE RATE US & LEAVE COMMENTS - we would love to hear from you !!!  Or email me at photomama5@sbcglobal.net or join our MYSPACE group at http://groups.myspace.com/photomama !!  Also - if you are interested in more info on the original Hamster Dance go to HAMSTERDANCE2.com  They rock.  To answer some of your questions - yes doing it in public is CRAZY.  People kept laughing at us, and staring, and some people didn't care.  It was a lot of fun!  One of the scenes in the video we were in a GLASS elevator, so each level people were staring and laughing it was soo funny.  Then .. in the middle of Sam's Club breakdancing, that was the ultimate!  Enjoy!  New answer to question :  why Master Chief from Halo in the middle of the video?  CUZ MASTER CHIEF AND HALO ROCK!! DUH!

title: The Randy Bandits - Story Of Your Life (shower a capella)
description: Having spent the past four years bringing serious doses of heartfelt, mind-bending, tastefully indulgent melodious joy to New York area concert stages, THE RANDY BANDITS are going on record with their unique brand of genuine American music for their first full-length CD, REDBEARD.  Produced by revered pop craftsman Richard X. Heyman with Nancy Leigh and Spiff Wiegand and mixed by Kurt Reil of the Gripweeds, REDBEARD combines the genre-defying musicality of The Band, the earthy sincerity of Wilco and The Jayhawks, and the quirky pop smarts of Ben Folds Five and Guster for a welcome respite from the irony, detachment and jadedness found in much of today's new music. THE RANDY BANDITS will be hosting a CD Release Party for REDBEARD Friday, Feb. 17 in the Tap Bar at the Knitting Factory, 74 Leonard St., New York City. Show time is 8 p.m., with Byron Isaacs of Ollabelle and Tom Warnick opening. Tickets $10. Info: 212-219-3132 or www.knittingfactory.com.  REDBEARD encapsulates THE RANDY BANDITS' quest to put out new music in an entertaining way, to captivate fans (a.k.a. Fandits) with sincerity as well as lunacy, and to do something meaningful in a culture and business currently deluged with artifice and irony. The songs on REDBEARD swing from Rock to Country to Bluegrass to Jazz to Soul to Blues to Gospel with lots of hybrids, a jillion instruments traded amongst the musicians, and soaring vocal harmonies. The band's lyrics reflect the sensibility of their leader, award-winning playwright-turned-songwriter Jim Knable ("Spain"), who sings, plays acoustic guitar and sax, and is joined in THE RANDY BANDITS by Russ Kaplan (keyboards, vocals), Stephen Aleman (vocals, percussion), Spiff Wiegand (vocals, trumpet, mandolin, electric guitar, accordion and more), Chris Murphy (bass, vocals, electric guitar) and Adam Farrell (drums).  Together, they've focused attention to arrangement and performance since THE RANDY BANDITS' 2003 EP, The Woman ... or the Blues. The folky abandon has been left behind, but the spontaneity and downright madness their audiences love remains in full force.  We're sincere musical adventurers who believe in connecting to our audience with fun, humor and humanity," says Knable. "We're not ironic. We're not about pop culture trendiness. We're about making really lasting music."  REDBEARD is available through www.randybandits.com, www.cdbaby.com, www.amazon.com and exclusively in Manhattan at The Mudtruck on Wall Street and in Brooklyn at Soundtracks on 7th Ave.

title: kangaroos
description: eeeek! sorry..I didnt know that it will be plugged here n tube..I just uploaded that n tube to stick it to my web page so that my friends n my country can see..coz they keep asking me bout kangaroos eversince I arrived here n Australia..And the next thing happened is dat I received sooo many e-mails regarding comments from tube and its sux! It ruined my morning... But tenks to all who sent comments that its cute and kewl!Coz for me its truly a great video, to catch a kangaroo wherein shes n a state of scratching herself haha! To those who made bad comments..I wish I did not erase the video wherein I caught a kangaroo jacking off. I think that video would be a good entertainment for them..doh! To those who are asking where it is...It's in Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary Goldcoast Australia...Well the kangaroos look anorexic, skinny or inactive as how u describe them grrr! because some of them are sick! That is why they're there at the wildlife hospital...and because of that they are not capable of kicking a butt or wat did u say?? asses??? they can't attack people...and they are also well-behaved kangaroos...and to those who say It's boring to take video in a Zoo well..for me its not a Zoo just to display animals...IT'S A SANCTUARYS.. meaning "HOLY" It's a consecrative place..has a sacred purpose with Tranquility and Security...and also giv people a chance to have a face to face with them...wake up man!There are no places on earth that are not altered by man..It would be unbearable to think of a world in which the most majestic of the creatures of the land are no longer existed...Lucky we have sanctuaries to care and preserve them...

It ruined my morning... But tenks to all who sent comments that its cute and kewl!Coz for me its truly a great video, to catch a kangaroo wherein shes n a state of scratching herself haha! To those who made bad comments..I wish I did not erase the video wherein I caught a kangaroo jacking off. I think that video would be a good entertainment for them..doh! To those who are asking where it is...It's in Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary Goldcoast Australia...Well the kangaroos look anorexic, skinny or inactive as how u describe them grrr! because some of them are sick! That is why they're there at the wildlife hospital...and because of that they are not capable of kicking a butt or wat did u say?? asses??? they can't attack people...and they are also well-behaved kangaroos...and to those who say It's boring to take video in a Zoo well..for me its not a Zoo just to display animals...IT'S A SANCTUARYS.. meaning "HOLY" It's a consecrative place..has a sacred purpose with Tranquility and Security...and also giv people a chance to have a face to face with them...wake up man!There are no places on earth that are not altered by man..It would be unbearable to think of a world in which the most majestic of the creatures of the land are no longer existed...Lucky we have sanctuaries to care and preserve them...

title: Large hornet on hand
description: This giant hornet was my pet for 7 months. Here she climbs onto my fingers and enjoys a snack of honey.  Note: This is not a Japanese giant hornet (Vespa mandarinia), but a Vespa ducalis, which comes really close in size. It is not a male, as someone claimed, it's a worker. Note the antennae and abdomen - males have an additional segment and a blunt abdomen, and long curved antennae. Their usual lifespan is merely several weeks, which is why I'm surprised myself. She isn't flying simply because she's busy eating. I caught her intending just to take some photos, but decided to keep her later. This is not in any way related to the cicada killer, it is a close relative of the European hornet Vespa crabro and the previously mentioned Japanese giant hornet. They never attack away from the nest. And yes, I have been stung by this species (but not this individual); it hurts somewhat; swollen hand, stiff fingers, but no lasting effect. She died naturally of old age.   Note also that this video is only to document how docile they can be away from the nest, and also the size of this magnificent insect.

description: John Fowler playing the fiddle in the Carolina Appalachian Old Timey Style It's called Old-Time. The fiddle, not violin is crossed tuned AEAE. title: Re-Enactment: The Princess Bride
description: The Seventh of my Re-enactment series.  Holy balls, this one took a while to finish, mainly because of the size. It clocked in as a whole gig when I had it as an .AVI.  This is the "Battle of Wits" scene from The Princess Bride. A mysterious man in black has been chasing three criminals who have kidnapped a princess. He has beaten a swordsman and a giant. Now all that's left is outsmarting the genius of the group, Vizzini, in a battle of wits.  Here's a list of what I used, and what they were supposed to represent in the scene.  My mask = a pair of boxers with holes cut in them My moustache = a brown-colored toothpick scotch-taped to my face Wine = Iced tea Wine bottle = a gallon of iced tea The Princess (scene briefly on the right of the screen near the beginning) = a rocking horse with a red shirt on it  Five minutes long... this is definitely the longest one. Enjoy.

description: LUCKY NUMBER SLEVIN is a thriller that twists and turns its way through an underworld of crime and revenge. Set in New York City, a case of mistaken identity lands Slevin (Josh Hartnett) into the middle of a war being plotted by two of the city's most rival crime bosses: The Rabbi (Ben Kingsley) and The Boss (Morgan Freeman). Slevin is under constant surveillance by relentless Detective Brikowski (Stanley Tucci) as well as the infamous assassin Goodkat (Bruce Willis) and finds himself having to hatch his own ingenious plot to get them...before they get him. Also starring Lucy Liu, LUCKY NUMBER SLEVIN is directed by Paul McGuigan and written by Jason Smilovic

title: Re-Enactment: The Princess Bride
description: The Seventh of my Re-enactment series.  Holy balls, this one took a while to finish, mainly because of the size. It clocked in as a whole gig when I had it as an .AVI.  This is the "Battle of Wits" scene from The Princess Bride. A mysterious man in black has been chasing three criminals who have kidnapped a princess. He has beaten a swordsman and a giant. Now all that's left is outsmarting the genius of the group, Vizzini, in a battle of wits. ------------------------------ -------------- RECENT QUESTIONS AND STATEMENTS ANSWERED:  Yes, that is my actual voice. (Wtf?)  Yes, I realize that there is a glaring continuity error, and I hit myself for not noticing it. I didn't go back and fix it for two reasons:  1. I didn't feel like it. 2. It was only a small continuity error, and I'm not trying to focus on getting the scene picture perfect to the original. I'm focusing on the acting and dialogue.  I know I fell the wrong way. There was a desk to my right. I would have collided with it. ------------------------------ --------------  Here's a list of what I used, and what they were supposed to represent in the scene.  My mask = a pair of boxers with holes cut in them My moustache = a brown-colored toothpick scotch-taped to my face Wine = Iced tea Wine bottle = a tupperware container The Princess (scene briefly on the right of the screen near the beginning) = a rocking horse with a red shirt on it  Five minutes long... this is definitely the longest one. Enjoy.

title: NUDE HIPPO: YOUR CHICAGO SHOW (The Gadget Guy: Time change)
description: THE BIG FAT NUDE HIPPO SHOW premiered on Chicago Cable-Access on May 3, 1997 and quickly received attention from viewers, the media and even won a few local prestigious awards. On April 1, 1999 the weekly program moved up to the Commercial Cable Channel (25) and matured into NUDE HIPPO: YOUR CHICAGO SHOW.  Coming up on 9 years, NUDE HIPPO: YOUR CHICAGO SHOW is the best source for finding great people, fun locations, and cool events in the Chicagoland area! As an off-beat family-oriented comedy/talk show, NUDE HIPPO offers a fresh look at the local culture and special events unique to Chicago.  Unlike any other local program, NUDE HIPPO has the strongest media connections, a loyal (and growing) following, and an established and well-respected relationships showcasing Simply Chicago's Best on the hottest night of primetime television, Thursdays from 7-8 pm.  Visit www.NudeHippo.com for more info & fun!  ------------------------------ ---------------- Leave a comment and we'll read them on the air and post the video here and at www.NudeHippo.com this Thursday night!  Don't hold back, tell us what you really think.  We appreciate all of the kind words so far.  ------------------------------ ----------------

title: Vokor vs.Grimrott: Belegarth Spring War 2006
description: Vokor vs. Grimrott: Mongolian wrestling, at Spring War 2006 - a Belegarth event. Belegarth is a Medieval Combat Sport, to learn more about it check out: www.belegarth.com. This was a video of some wrestling on the sidelines in between battles. The difference between what we do and what LARPers do is that we focus on the combat and are full force, full contact - it's an athletic martial sport vs. being a bunch of D&D; geeks out in the woods tap fighting. Vokor in real life is an MMA combatant, Grimrott is a martial arts instructor. It had been raining on and off at this event, because of the mud Grimrott's knee pops in this video damaging his MCL/ACL. It should take 2-8 weeks to heal.

title: Josh Daiek at the Extremes
description: Josh Daiek skiing an amazing run at the 2005 "Extremes" at Kirkwood Mountain Resort in Kirkwood, California.  Every year Kirkwood hosts the final stop of the North American Feeskiing Championships.  Skiers and riders compete on "The Cirque", a large vertical cliff of volcanic rock and chutes closed to the public all season due to how dangerous the terrain is.  In this video clip Josh Daiek, a Kirkwood local "home boy", puts in an incredible run on the first day of the 2005 competition.  Another local Kirkwood skier, Craig Gabriel, went on to win the overall competition.

title: Cockroach Controlled Mobile Robot
description: By Garnet Hertz (2005)                                                                               "Cockroach Controlled Mobile Robot" is an experimental mechanism that uses a living Madagascan hissing cockroach atop a modified trackball to control a three-wheeled robot. If the cockroach moves left, the robot moves left. Infrared sensors also provide navigation feedback to the cockroach, striving to create a pseudo-intelligent system with the cockroach as the CPU.

title: TotalVid Frosted Flakes Video Podcast
description: Max Henault's part from Frosted Flakes.  From one of the coldest city in the world comes one of the best snowboard movie of the season. Frosted Flakes is a 16mm motion picture film featuring the most technical and stylish jibs ever seen on a shred stick. This 25-minutes presentation is packed with some next -level tricks, performed by some upcoming talents as well as some top international riders. Frosted Flakes brings a new artistic direction into the sport. With it's unique cinematography and editing style, this movie is destined to become a classic in every snowboarder's library.  Starring: Yan Dofin, Max Legend, Danny Kass, Max Heneault, Risto Matilla, Antti Autti, Jf Fortin, Matt Dano, US Open, Shakedown and many more crazy snowboard stunt entertainners.

title: Art Film...
description: ...ha! More like I've just been fiddling with this for 5 minutes here at my diningroom table. I appreciate all the comments - but may I again stress that this is not serious, or really an "art film", so chill!  As you can see, I have recently discovered the joys of windows movie maker. I'm basically fiddling around with some of the effects.  As for the pics: the first one is of me, next it's Port Stanley, then Brady, me and Brady, a distorted picture I took at Sharon's creek, my eyes, Lake Margaret and me and Brady in Port Stanley.  For those who asked: the main premise is pretty simple: boy and girl have been having problems, boy and girl work it out (sorta). Relatable, n'est pas?  Music: Out of Focus - Buck 65

title: Cockroach Controlled Mobile Robot
description: By Garnet Hertz (2005)                                                                               "Cockroach Controlled Mobile Robot" is an experimental mechanism that uses a living Madagascan hissing cockroach atop a modified trackball to control a three-wheeled robot. If the cockroach moves left, the robot moves left. Infrared sensors also provide navigation feedback to the cockroach, striving to create a pseudo-intelligent system with the cockroach as the CPU.

title: TotalVid Frosted Flakes Video Podcast
description: Max Henault's part from Frosted Flakes.  From one of the coldest city in the world comes one of the best snowboard movie of the season. Frosted Flakes is a 16mm motion picture film featuring the most technical and stylish jibs ever seen on a shred stick. This 25-minutes presentation is packed with some next -level tricks, performed by some upcoming talents as well as some top international riders. Frosted Flakes brings a new artistic direction into the sport. With it's unique cinematography and editing style, this movie is destined to become a classic in every snowboarder's library.  Starring: Yan Dofin, Max Legend, Danny Kass, Max Heneault, Risto Matilla, Antti Autti, Jf Fortin, Matt Dano, US Open, Shakedown and many more crazy snowboard stunt entertainners.

title: Josh Daiek at the Extremes
description: Josh Daiek skiing an amazing run at the 2005 "Extremes" at Kirkwood Mountain Resort in Kirkwood, California.  Every year Kirkwood hosts the final stop of the North American Feeskiing Championships.  Skiers and riders compete on "The Cirque", a large vertical cliff of volcanic rock and chutes closed to the public all season due to how dangerous the terrain is.  In this video clip Josh Daiek, a Kirkwood local "home boy", puts in an incredible run on the first day of the 2005 competition.  Another local Kirkwood skier, Craig Gabriel, went on to win the overall competition.

title: Official Clerks II Trailer
description: A calamity at Dante and Randall's shops sends them looking for new horizons - but they ultimately settle at Mooby's, a fictional Disney-McDonald's-style fast-food empire. Free from his dead-end job (and lodged in a new one), Dante begins to break free of his rut, planning to move away with his clingy fiancé. Dante is ready to leave the horrors of minimum-wage New Jersey behind, but Randal - always the more hostile of the two - starts to become overwhelmed by his own rancor.

title: Exclusive clip - Clerks II "Making of" intro by Kevin Smith
description: This version is fixed and does not stop in the middle. If you watched the first one and had problems - please load up this one. Thanks.  Visit Clerks2.com and myspace.com/clerksII  Picking up ten years after "Clerks" left off, "Clerks II" looks in on Dante and Randal's semi-new life (or lack thereof). Jeff Anderson and Brian O'Halloran star, along with Rosario Dawson, Trevor Fehrman and Jennifer Schwalbach. Jason Mewes and Kevin Smith return as Jay and Silent Bob

description: An MGM release of a Weinstein Company presented movie, LUCKY NUMBER SLEVIN is a thriller that twists and turns its way through an underworld of crime and revenge. Set in New York City, a case of mistaken identity lands Slevin (Josh Hartnett) into the middle of a war being plotted by two of the city's most rival crime bosses: The Rabbi (Ben Kingsley) and The Boss (Morgan Freeman). Slevin is under constant surveillance by relentless Detective Brikowski (Stanley Tucci) as well as the infamous assassin Goodkat (Bruce Willis) and finds himself having to hatch his own ingenious plot to get them...before they get him. Also starring Lucy Liu, LUCKY NUMBER SLEVIN is directed by Paul McGuigan and written by Jason Smilovic

title: Pet Tricks
description: Paul Papanek (that's him in the video) explains: "[Oscar the dog] came up with this little trick all on on his own, though we have worked together to kind of hone it to the fine skill it is. Letterman flew us out to NY to be on Stupid Pet Tricks just about a year ago. After having successfully gone through rehearsal, we were sitting in the green room waiting to go on - along with a couple of other dogs and a pig - and someone came in and told us that Dave had decided that he wasn't in the mood for Pet Tricks that night after all (he really wanted to spend more time talking to Sting...)"
